article.description: B.J. Johnson scored 22 points, Jordan Price added 20 points, nine boards and three steals, and La Salle beat Bucknell 83-73 on Saturday to snap the Bison's four-game win streak.
article.headline: Johnson, Price send La Salle past Bucknell 83-73
article.linkText: Johnson, Price send La Salle past Bucknell 83-73
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- B.J. Johnson scored 22 points, Jordan Price added 20 points, nine boards and three steals, and La Salle beat Bucknell 83-73 on Saturday to snap the Bison's four-game win streak. Price's jumper tied the game at 44 early in the second half and Johnson's dunk 30 seconds later gave La Salle (4-2) the lead for good and its third straight win. Johnson's 3 with 13:24 remaining put the Explorers up 58-48. Bucknell, which led 44-42 at halftime, never got the deficit to fewer than 10. Johnson made another 3 at the 10:15 mark to push the lead to 67-51. La Salle was 8 for 16 from 3-point range. The Bison shot 58.6 percent in the first half but just 39 percent after the break. Stephen Brown had 15 points and six assists, and Nate Jones scored a career-high 15 points for Bucknell (6-3).
